<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-267-778  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 267 778.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Publish!andP;  June 1989 v4 n6 p112(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A scanner in the works. (desktop publishing) (End Paper) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Felici, James.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>At Publish magazine, the scanner is not used so much as aproduction tool as it is a design tool.andP;  Halftones on a scannerare more expensive than traditional ones.andP;  Jagged edges on scannedline art make using a scanner for production disappointing.andO;Predicting the print quality of scanned images is also a problem.andO;At Publish, the scanner is used for creating 'for position only'photostats for layouts and comps.andP;  A scanner is particularlyhelpful when working on the cover design.andP;  Making revisions andalterations to designs are quicker with a scanner.andP;  By scanning atlow resolution (72dpi), the screen and printer run faster.andP;  Usinga scanner for design only may make justification for buying ascanner more difficult.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ScanningDesktop PublishingDocument PreparationPhotographyLayout.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>